/// hero bg:primary text:light
h1: Build what comes next.
p: Frontline Summit brings together 1,200 product, design, and engineering leaders for three days of talks, workshops, and honest conversations about how software gets made.
p: March 12–14, 2025 · Chicago
button: Register now -> /register
btn-secondary: View schedule -> /schedule

/// section
h2: This year's tracks

col:
  icon: bi bi-cpu
  h3: Platform Engineering
  p: Developer experience, internal platforms, and the golden path between speed and stability.

col:
  icon: bi bi-palette
  h3: Product Design at Scale
  p: Design systems, accessibility debt, and leading creative work in a fast-moving org.

col:
  icon: bi bi-people
  h3: Leadership & Culture
  p: Hiring, retention, psychological safety, and building teams that survive hypergrowth.

/// section bg:muted
h2: Formats

col:
  h3: Keynotes
  p: Six 45-minute talks from practitioners who've shipped things that mattered.

col:
  h3: Deep-dive workshops
  p: Half-day sessions capped at 30 attendees. Hands-on, no slides, all practice.

col:
  h3: Open hallway track
  p: Unscheduled space for spontaneous conversations. Some of the best talks happen here.


